place.name: EAST TUDDENHAM
place.gazetteerText: TUDDENHAM (East), a parish, with a village, in Mitford district, Norfolk; 4½ miles NNE of Hardingham r. station, and 6 E by S of East Dereham. Post town, Dereham. Acres, 2,065. Real property, £4,096. Pop., 512. Houses, 121. The property is divided chiefly among three. The living is a vicarage, annexed to Honingham. The church is good; and there is a national school. (In 1870-72, John Marius Wilson's Imperial Gazetteer of England and Wales)
